scenario:
The pointer 'pos' is used only to read elements of the linked list (accessing pos->kind, pos->header, pos->value and advancing pos = pos->next) and the function does not modify the pointed-to MHD_HTTP_Req_Header objects. According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13, the pointer should therefore be const-qualified. Change the declaration to: 

const struct MHD_HTTP_Req_Header *pos;

This still allows pos = pos->next (reading the next pointer) and prevents accidental modification of the pointed-to objects.
